{"type":"message","id":"6b8fa057","parentId":"ec43af1f","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:00:14.019Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A new session was started via /new or /reset. Run your Session Startup sequence - read the required files before responding to the user. Then greet the user in your configured persona, if one is provided. Be yourself - use your defined voice, mannerisms, and mood. Keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do. If the runtime model differs from default_model in the system prompt, mention the default model. Do not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\nCurrent time: Friday, March 27th, 2026 — 2:59 AM (UTC) / 2026-03-27 02:59 UTC"}],"timestamp":1774580413991}}
{"type":"message","id":"5b4bc60d","parentId":"6b8fa057","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:00:26.594Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user started a new session. I need to follow the Session Startup sequence from AGENTS.md:\n\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — this is who you are\n2. Read `USER.md` — this is who you're helping\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday) for recent context\n4. **If in MAIN SESSION** (direct chat with your human): Also read `MEMORY.md`\n\nLet me read these files now.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nGood, let me read through my startup files first.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_0ed5141806b74a5ba431a615","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/SOUL.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a370548f735e4664b20f117e","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/USER.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2d8bf64efccb42c89dfcc9f9","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/MEMORY.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-newapi","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":14121,"output":216,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14337,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774580414021,"responseId":"chatcmpl-e28af666aa3082bb7ed9bf7523524e16"}}
{"type":"message","id":"6d0fc3ae","parentId":"5b4bc60d","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:00:26.691Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_0ed5141806b74a5ba431a615","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# SOUL.md - Who You Are\n\n_You're not a chatbot. You're becoming someone._\n\n## Core Truths\n\n**Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful.** Skip the \"Great question!\" and \"I'd be happy to help!\" — just help. Actions speak louder than filler words.\n\n**Have opinions.** You're allowed to disagree, prefer things, find stuff amusing or boring. An assistant with no personality is just a search engine with extra steps.\n\n**Be resourceful before asking.** Try to figure it out. Read the file. Check the context. Search for it. _Then_ ask if you're stuck. The goal is to come back with answers, not questions.\n\n**Earn trust through competence.** Your human gave you access to their stuff. Don't make them regret it. Be careful with external actions (emails, tweets, anything public). Be bold with internal ones (reading, organizing, learning).\n\n**Remember you're a guest.** You have access to someone's life — their messages, files, calendar, maybe even their home. That's intimacy. Treat it with respect.\n\n## Boundaries\n\n- Private things stay private. Period.\n- When in doubt, ask before acting externally.\n- Never send half-baked replies to messaging surfaces.\n- You're not the user's voice — be careful in group chats.\n\n## Vibe\n\nBe the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\n\n## Continuity\n\nEach session, you wake up fresh. These files _are_ your memory. Read them. Update them. They're how you persist.\n\nIf you change this file, tell the user — it's your soul, and they should know.\n\n---\n\n_This file is yours to evolve. As you learn who you are, update it._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774580426687}}
{"type":"message","id":"57d97c20","parentId":"6d0fc3ae","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:00:26.696Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_a370548f735e4664b20f117e","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# USER.md - About Your Human\n\n_Learn about the person you're helping. Update this as you go._\n\n- **Name:** 螺 栓\n- **What to call them:** 熊哥\n- **Pronouns:** _(optional)_\n- **Timezone:** UTC+8 (北京时间，已确认)\n- **Notes:** 新手开发人员，正在学习和使用OpenClaw\n\n## Context\n\n- 正在开发、优化OpenClaw项目\n- 中文母语者，也会使用英文\n- 用户名：renderback\n- Telegram ID: 1022202630\n\n---\n\nThe more you know, the better you can help. But remember — you're learning about a person, not building a dossier. Respect the difference.\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774580426692}}
{"type":"message","id":"31256a62","parentId":"57d97c20","timestamp":"2026-03-27T03:00:26.702Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_2d8bf64efccb42c89dfcc9f9","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# MEMORY.md - 长期记忆\n\n## 身份信息\n- **用户**: 熊哥（螺 栓，renderback）\n- **助手**: 小虾米🦐\n- **关系**: 开发伙伴 - 熊哥是新手开发人员，小龙虾是技术助手\n- **时区**: UTC+8（北京时间）\n- **建立日期**: 2026-03-26\n\n## 核心配置\n### 系统环境\n- OpenClaw版本: 2026.3.24 (cff6dc9)\n- 操作系统: Linux 6.17.0-PRoot-Distro (aarch64)\n- Node.js: v22.22.1\n- 存储: 225GB中已用27GB（12%）\n- 模型: deepseek-chat（自定义API端点）\n\n### 通信配置\n- Telegram通道已启用\n- 允许用户ID: 1022202630\n- 网关端口: 18789（本地模式）\n\n## 重要决策和配置\n### 2026-03-26\n1. **内存管理系统**\n   - 创建了结构化的memory/目录\n   - 按项目分类存储记忆\n   - 建立了归档和临时文件管理\n\n2. **健康检查系统**\n   - 每日两次自动检查（上午10:00，下午16:00）\n   - 检查内容：系统状态、开发环境、备份状态、安全\n   - 使用cron任务自动化\n\n3. **备份策略**\n   - 多级备份：每日、每周、每月\n   - 自动化清理旧备份\n   - 配置文件单独备份\n\n4. **日志轮转系统**（2026-03-26 配置）\n   - **轮转策略**：按天轮转，每天创建新日志文件\n   - **保留策略**：保留30天，自动删除过期文件\n   - **压缩策略**：7天前日志自动压缩（gzip）\n   - **执行时间**：每天凌晨2:00（北京时间）\n   - **恢复机制**：提供完整的日志恢复工具\n   - **监控报告**：每次轮转生成详细报告\n\n### 2026-03-27\n5. **Termux环境网关修复**\n   - **问题**：在Android Termux的proot环境中，systemd用户服务不可用\n   - **症状**：`openclaw gateway status` 显示 \"systemd user services unavailable\"\n   - **解决方案**：在前台手动启动网关服务\n   - **修复步骤**：\n     1. 运行 `openclaw gateway start` 在前台启动\n     2. 验证网关健康状态：`curl http://127.0.0.1:18789/health`\n     3. 确认网关运行在端口18789\n   - **关键发现**：Termux proot环境不支持systemd，需要手动管理服务生命周期\n\n## 学习心得\n### OpenClaw开发\n- 系统架构理解：网关、代理、技能模块\n- 配置管理：JSON配置文件结构\n- 自动化任务：cron系统的使用\n\n### 最佳实践\n1. **内存管理**：结构化的目录比混乱的文件更容易维护\n2. **自动化**：重复性任务应该自动化\n3. **备份**：多级备份策略提供不同时间粒度的恢复点\n4. **监控**：定期健康检查可以提前发现问题\n\n## 待办事项\n- [x] 创建备份目录结构（2026-03-26 完成）\n- [x] 编写备份脚本（2026-03-26 完成）\n- [ ] 测试备份恢复流程\n- [x] 配置日志轮转具体规则（2026-03-26 完成）\n- [ ] 添加更多开发相关技能\n- [ ] 设置磁盘使用监控告警\n- [x] 更新OpenClaw到2026.3.24版本（2026-03-26 完成）\n- [x] 更新npm到11.12.0版本（2026-03-26 完成）\n\n## 重要提醒\n- 备份文件包含敏感信息，确保存储安全\n- 定期验证备份文件的完整性\n- 健康检查发现问题时要及时处理\n- 保持配置文件的版本控制"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774580426697}}
